remarks:
Is it 'a-dimplebo' or 'ad-implebo'? Books don't agree:

1) ad-implebo: Liber Gradualis 1983 and 1895, Paroissien Romain 1903, Graduale Vatican 1908, Graduale Romanum Pustet 1911, Liber Usualis 1924 (round notes), Graduale Romanum Schwann 1953, Liber Brevior 1954, Liber Usualis 1961, Graduel Neumé 1966

2) a-dimplebo: Mass and Vespers 1957, Graduale Romanum 1961, Graduale Romanum 1974

remarks:
Is it 'pot-entiam' or 'po-tentiam'? (also 'omnipot-ens' vs. 'omnipo-tens')

1) pot-entiam: Solesmes 1908 onward (Graduale Solesmes 1908, Liber Brevior 1954, 1961 books, etc.)

2) po-tentiam: Solesmes pre-1908 (Liber Gradualis 1895, Liber Usualis 1903, etc.) and all non-Solesmes books I can find (Graduale Vatican 1908, Pustet, Mechlin, Schwann, O.P. etc.)
